---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro'
---

<BaseLayout title="Sugarloaf Mountain & Abergavenny - Welsh Hikes">

  <header class="hero">
    <div class="hero-overlay">
      <h1>Sugarloaf Mountain</h1>
      <p class="hero-sub">Abergavenny, South Wales</p>
    </div>
  </header>

  <div class="post-wrapper">
    <div class="post-container">

      <div class="meta">
        <span>📍 Abergavenny</span>
        <span>📏 10km</span>
        <span>🥾 Moderate to difficult</span>
        <span>⛺ Camping trip</span>
      </div>

      <img class="hero-photo" src="/images/abergavenny_view_park.jpeg" alt="Sugarloaf Mountain" />

      <div class="post-body">
        <div class="text-block">

          <h2 class="section-heading">The Walk</h2>

          <p>
            In late summer, when the weather is getting colder but the sun is still shining 
            and sun cream should still be at hand, a group of eight of us headed to Abergavenny 
            for a camping weekend. The destination was chosen partly for the location and partly 
            because Sugarloaf Mountain is a name you cannot ignore, it sounds like 
            somewhere you have to visit.
          </p>
          <p>
            The walk begins from a large car park overlooking rolling Welsh fields where all 
            sorts of farm animals graze. There are glimpses of small towns with distinctive pubs on 
            the horizon, but nothing close enough to clearly make out. There's a clear cut path through long 
            grass leads that you straight towards the mountain, and although it does not initially 
            look like the path is heading anywhere obvious, the mountain is so inviting that 
            you just follow it. And it is absolutely the right way.
          </p>
          <p>
            The first half of the hike switches between steep climbs, flat stretches and 
            downward sections winding through large trees, rivers and fern. Forage, carving on trees,
            and the sound of nature is everywhere, it is a diverse walk that keeps you interested.
          </p>
          <p>
            Then comes the mountain itself. A roughly two kilometre climb upwards. When 
            the weather is clear, each step reveals more of the surrounding valley below you. 
            To have some fun and keep spirits high we played the alphabet game — a simple but 
            effective way to pass the time on a long climb. The aim is to greet 
            every person you pass on the hike using a word beginning with the next letter of 
            the alphabet, working from A to Z as a group.
          </p>
          <p>
            At the summit you are met with a large stone carved into the mountain that's brilliant 
            for photos. The peak itself is small with steep edges dropping away on all sides, 
            which makes for a impressive picnic spot to sit on the edge and take the view in.
          </p>
          <p>
            The walk back is potentially the most magical part, winding through large trees 
            over a soft mossy ground. It is easy to lose your way, but that is half the charm.
          </p>

        </div>
      </div>

      <img class="mid-photo" src="/images/abergavenny_foggy_mountain.jpeg" alt="Views from Sugarloaf Mountain" />

      <div class="post-body">
        <div class="text-block">

          <h2 class="section-heading">The Camping</h2>

          <p>
            Pyscodlyn Farm campsite is a large open field split into two, one side for 
            campers, one for caravanners. At the entrance sits an old stone building where 
            the farmer and owner of the site lives. There are toilets, showers and a 
            recreational room covering all the camping essentials. Controlled fires are allowed, 
            and depending on your neighbours you may well make friends.
          </p>
          <p>
            There is a river near the site that makes for a great short walk, although there is
            no true path there, with some exploring and some consideration for the cows and horses
            that eat in the nearb fields, it's easily reached. It makes a perfect spot for a BBQ
            and watching the sun go down.
          </p>

        </div>

        <div class="side-photo">
          <img src="/images/abergavenny_sunset.jpeg" alt="Pyscodlyn campsite" />
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="links">
        <a class="route-link" href="https://www.outdooractive.com/en/route/hiking-trail/south-wales/the-sugar-loaf-from-near-abergavenny/290849219/" target="_blank">
          View Walk Route
        </a>
        <a class="route-link secondary" href="https://maps.google.com/maps?vet=10CAAQoqAOahcKEwjQn8SAlvqTAxUAAAAAHQAAAAAQCA..i&sca_esv=31d988af6d9099b2&client=safari&hs=s7O&pvq=CgsvZy8xdHg4c25xbiIPCgljYW1wc2l0ZXMQAhgD&lqi=ChVhYmVyZ2F2ZW5ueSBjYW1wc2l0ZXNI1KWxxOeAgIAIWh8QARgAIhVhYmVyZ2F2ZW5ueSBjYW1wc2l0ZXMqAggDkgEKY2FtcGdyb3VuZJoBJENoZERTVWhOTUc5blMwVkpRMEZuU1VOUGFHTnRVM0JSUlJBQvoBBQizARA_&fvr=1&cs=0&um=1&ie=UTF-8&fb=1&gl=uk&sa=X&ftid=0x4871d7128f51b3a9:0x70110cf66b9a3886" target="_blank">
          View Campsite
        </a>
      </div>

    </div>
  </div>

</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .hero {
    height: 30vh;
    min-height: 400px;
    background-image: url("/images/abergavenny_mirror.jpeg");
    background-size: cover;
    background-position: center center;
    background-repeat: no-repeat;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    border-bottom-left-radius: 50% 8%;
    border-bottom-right-radius: 50% 8%;
    overflow: hidden;
    position: relative;
  }

  .hero::before {
    content: '';
    position: absolute;
    top: 0; left: 0; right: 0; bottom: 0;
    background: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.35);
    z-index: 1;
  }

  .hero-overlay {
    padding: 40px 60px;
    text-align: center;
    z-index: 2;
    position: relative;
  }

  .hero h1 {
    color: white;
    font-size: 3.5rem;
    font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;
    margin: 0;
  }

  .hero-sub {
    color: rgba(255,255,255,0.85);
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;
    margin: 8px 0 0 0;
  }

  .post-wrapper {
    background-color: #f9f9f9;
    padding: 60px 20px;
    min-height: 100vh;
    box-sizing: border-box;
  }

  .post-container {
    max-width: 900px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
    color: #333;
  }

  .meta {
    display: flex;
    gap: 24px;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    font-size: 1rem;
    color: #555;
    margin-bottom: 28px;
  }

  .hero-photo {
    width: 100%;
    max-height: 500px;
    object-fit: cover;
    border-radius: 12px;
    box-shadow: 0 4px 20px rgba(0,0,0,0.12);
    margin-bottom: 40px;
    object-position: center 30%;
  }

  .mid-photo {
    width: 100%;
    max-height: 450px;
    object-fit: cover;
    border-radius: 12px;
    box-shadow: 0 4px 20px rgba(0,0,0,0.12);
    margin: 10px 0 40px 0;
  }

  .post-body {
    display: flex;
    gap: 40px;
    align-items: flex-start;
    margin-bottom: 28px;
  }

  .text-block {
    flex: 1;
  }

  .section-heading {
    font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;
    font-size: 1.4rem;
    color: #003366;
    margin: 0 0 16px 0;
  }

  .text-block p {
    font-size: 1.05rem;
    line-height: 1.85;
    margin-bottom: 20px;
  }

  .side-photo {
    flex: 0 0 280px;
  }

  .side-photo img {
    width: 100%;
    border-radius: 10px;
    box-shadow: 0 4px 16px rgba(0,0,0,0.1);
    object-fit: cover;
  }

  .links {
    display: flex;
    gap: 16px;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    margin-top: 20px;
  }

  .route-link {
    display: inline-block;
    padding: 12px 24px;
    background-color: #003366;
    color: white;
    text-decoration: none;
    border-radius: 8px;
    font-size: 1rem;
    transition: background-color 0.3s;
  }

  .route-link:hover { background-color: #00509e; }

  .route-link.secondary {
    background-color: #4a7c59;
  }

  .route-link.secondary:hover { background-color: #3a6147; }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .post-body {
      flex-direction: column;
    }

    .side-photo {
      flex: 0 0 auto;
      width: 100%;
    }

    .hero h1 { font-size: 2rem; }
    .hero-overlay { padding: 20px; }

    .links {
      flex-direction: column;
    }

    .route-link {
      text-align: center;
    }
  }
</style>